01:11:28.716 --> 01:11:30.417
I think I'm gonna fire
my therapist.

01:11:30.417 --> 01:11:31.662
 ♪<i> Can you feel</i>
  <i> The love tonight?</i> ♪

01:11:41.662 --> 01:11:45.966
So, admit it.
You had fun.

01:11:45.966 --> 01:11:47.002
Okay, I did.

01:11:48.002 --> 01:11:50.877
Hey, look. I got you something
for helping me out with my knee.

01:11:57.612 --> 01:12:00.414
It's a compass.
You can wear it around
your neck on your trip.

01:12:00.414 --> 01:12:02.884
Just in case you don't know
which way to go.

01:12:02.884 --> 01:12:04.921
Thank you.

01:12:06.921 --> 01:12:09.391
Giving jewelry
is pretty serious, right?

01:12:10.391 --> 01:12:12.661
Well, I did work
pretty hard for it.

01:12:13.661 --> 01:12:16.632
So, I guess this means
it's finally time
to meet your dad?

01:12:18.632 --> 01:12:21.168
I don't know.
He's not too happy
about me bringing up

01:12:21.168 --> 01:12:23.506
how he gambled away
my college money.

01:12:25.506 --> 01:12:26.009
Oh.

01:12:28.009 --> 01:12:30.011
It's just not
the right time.

01:12:31.011 --> 01:12:32.948
It's never a good time.

01:12:33.948 --> 01:12:35.083
I can't do anything
about that.

01:12:36.083 --> 01:12:37.186
We're from two
different worlds.

01:12:39.186 --> 01:12:43.595
But I thought we were
gonna make our own
little world.

01:12:47.595 --> 01:12:48.530
I'll see what I can do.

01:12:49.530 --> 01:12:50.932
Okay.

01:12:51.932 --> 01:12:53.932
Hey, Pop.

01:12:51.932 --> 01:12:53.940
Hey.

01:12:59.940 --> 01:13:01.710
You smell like a barn.

01:13:02.710 --> 01:13:05.979
You've been spending
an awful lot of time
at the Grove's place.

01:13:05.979 --> 01:13:08.682
Yeah. They're helping me out
with my knee.

01:13:08.682 --> 01:13:10.854
They, or that girl?

01:13:12.854 --> 01:13:14.222
Don't start with me, Pop.

01:13:15.222 --> 01:13:17.560
Oh, so, you got you
a white girlfriend now.

01:13:18.560 --> 01:13:22.030
I have a girlfriend.
Her name is Lee.

01:13:23.030 --> 01:13:24.865
And I don't care about
the color of her skin.

01:13:24.865 --> 01:13:28.703
Well, I guarantee
she cares about
the color of your skin.

01:13:28.703 --> 01:13:31.739
Trust me. I've been
around this town too long.

01:13:32.739 --> 01:13:34.009
People are talking, Jordan,
about who did this

01:13:35.009 --> 01:13:37.514
and who did what between you
and them white boys.

01:13:39.514 --> 01:13:41.514
Well, Lee's different.

01:13:39.514 --> 01:13:41.916
She's no different.

01:13:41.916 --> 01:13:45.752
You think you're special?
You think she's gonna want
a future with you

01:13:45.752 --> 01:13:48.257
if can't play football,
if you can't afford school?

01:13:50.257 --> 01:13:52.094
You haven't even
told her, have you?

01:13:53.094 --> 01:13:54.929
I didn't think so.

01:13:54.929 --> 01:13:57.899
The second you don't have
some flashy future,
she's gonna drop you.

01:13:57.899 --> 01:14:01.502
You'll see.
She's got money, son.
Ain't nothing wrong with that.

01:14:01.502 --> 01:14:05.773
But she ain't gonna
wanna be with nobody
can't pay for her horses.

01:14:05.773 --> 01:14:08.773
That's just the way it is.

01:14:05.773 --> 01:14:08.510
You don't even know her.

01:14:08.510 --> 01:14:10.578
Because you're ashamed
to bring her around
your old man,

01:14:10.578 --> 01:14:12.212
because you figure
if she knows your roots,

01:14:12.212 --> 01:14:14.149
she might not stick around.

01:14:15.149 --> 01:14:18.686
-I'll bring her by, then.
-All right, you do that.

01:14:19.686 --> 01:14:23.686
I'm sure she's a...
she's a nice young lady.

01:14:19.686 --> 01:14:23.157
Yes, she is.

01:14:23.157 --> 01:14:25.029
But she's gonna
break your heart.

01:14:28.029 --> 01:14:29.269
She's not Mom.

01:14:34.269 --> 01:14:36.871
I'm just trying
to look out for you, son.

01:14:36.871 --> 01:14:39.908
You're from
separate worlds.

01:14:39.908 --> 01:14:41.966
Ain't no future
for the two of you.

01:15:05.966 --> 01:15:09.703
Looks like Jordan's all better.
Time to get back to work.

01:15:40.268 --> 01:15:42.337
See, whenever
you're steering him,

01:15:42.337 --> 01:15:44.204
if you want him
to go this way,

01:15:44.204 --> 01:15:46.341
you want to pull back
towards your hip.

01:15:46.341 --> 01:15:49.243
Just like that.
You never cross over his neck.

01:15:49.243 --> 01:15:51.078
So, bring him around
this way.

01:15:51.078 --> 01:15:52.880
Good. Now loosen up.

01:16:07.028 --> 01:16:12.220
Historians have
traditionally divided the war
into three phases.

01:16:32.220 --> 01:16:34.689
-Hey. You need any help?
-Hey.

01:16:35.689 --> 01:16:37.925
Yeah. Uh, maybe
you could grab a brush.

01:16:37.925 --> 01:16:40.925
I need to get ready
for school pretty soon.

01:16:37.925 --> 01:16:40.332
Yeah.

01:16:44.332 --> 01:16:48.872
Oh, yeah.
You like that, huh, boy?

01:16:50.872 --> 01:16:52.041
You look tired.

01:16:53.041 --> 01:16:55.010
Just what every woman
loves to hear.

01:16:56.010 --> 01:16:58.078
I just worry about you.

01:16:58.078 --> 01:16:59.783
You know,
you've been pushing hard.

01:17:01.783 --> 01:17:04.989
That's what you have to do
to accomplish your dreams.

01:17:08.989 --> 01:17:10.094
How you doing, Chief?

01:17:13.094 --> 01:17:14.434
You miss your buddy,
don't you?

01:17:19.434 --> 01:17:24.738
Hey, Lee, have you ever
really grieved Casey's death?

01:17:24.738 --> 01:17:25.474
Yeah. Of course.

01:17:26.474 --> 01:17:29.476
It just seems like
ever since it all happened,

01:17:29.476 --> 01:17:31.476
you've just been
running ragged, you know?

01:17:29.476 --> 01:17:31.912
I'm fine, Jordan.

01:17:31.912 --> 01:17:34.850
I don't know why you always
keep bringing it up.

01:17:35.850 --> 01:17:38.056
Okay. Never mind.

01:17:43.056 --> 01:17:44.760
Prom's coming up, right?

01:17:45.760 --> 01:17:46.461
Guess so.

01:17:46.461 --> 01:17:48.261
Do I, like, have to go to that?

01:17:48.261 --> 01:17:51.432
Or am I too old?
Will they let me in?

01:17:52.432 --> 01:17:55.802
I've never really cared
too much about prom, so...

01:17:55.802 --> 01:17:57.240
Okay, good.

01:18:00.240 --> 01:18:02.844
I know it doesn't compare...

01:18:02.844 --> 01:18:05.149
but I was thinking
I could invite you over
for dinner with my father.

01:18:09.149 --> 01:18:11.149
Really?

01:18:09.149 --> 01:18:11.386
Yeah. I think I'm ready.

01:18:12.386 --> 01:18:14.523
I don't know
what'll happen, but...

01:18:15.523 --> 01:18:18.395
I just want him to realize
that we're different.

01:18:21.395 --> 01:18:22.430
I'm sure I'll love him.

01:18:23.430 --> 01:18:26.403
And I can make him
love me.

01:18:29.403 --> 01:18:31.140
Come on, come on.
Keep up, keep up!

01:18:33.140 --> 01:18:35.480
Uh-uh. Careful.

01:18:40.480 --> 01:18:41.984
Good boy.

01:18:42.984 --> 01:18:45.421
Easy. Good boy.

01:18:47.421 --> 01:18:49.297
One more time. Come on.

01:18:59.533 --> 01:19:01.805
Looks like you've been
training those horses hard.

01:19:03.805 --> 01:19:04.876
Yep.

01:19:08.876 --> 01:19:10.378
You still planning
on doing that trip?

01:19:11.378 --> 01:19:13.914
Probably have to delay
a month or so,

01:19:13.914 --> 01:19:16.454
but, yeah, I am.

01:19:21.454 --> 01:19:23.257
You still gonna
ride it alone?

01:19:24.257 --> 01:19:25.363
Sure am.

01:19:30.363 --> 01:19:33.167
You know, you, um...
you actually proved me wrong.

01:19:34.167 --> 01:19:35.869
I thought
you'd lose interest.

01:19:35.869 --> 01:19:37.005
Like you did
when you were a kid
with the tree house.

01:19:38.005 --> 01:19:41.945
But...
you impressed me.

01:19:44.945 --> 01:19:46.948
Thanks, Dad.

01:19:47.948 --> 01:19:50.618
Listen, you know,
I know I haven't been
the best father lately.

01:19:50.618 --> 01:19:52.953
And you can take this
for whatever it's worth.

01:19:52.953 --> 01:19:54.288
But, um...

01:19:55.288 --> 01:19:57.261
I just don't want you
riding cross-country.

01:20:00.261 --> 01:20:04.931
Now, listen.
You're gonna be out there
all by yourself.

01:20:04.931 --> 01:20:08.502
Going across the country,
okay? It's not safe.

01:20:09.502 --> 01:20:12.212
I don't know
if I can handle losing
someone else in my family.

01:20:19.212 --> 01:20:20.997
Can you do that for me?

01:20:46.340 --> 01:20:47.608
Hey.

01:20:47.608 --> 01:20:50.278
Wow, you look great.
Are you ready for this?

01:20:50.278 --> 01:20:51.283
Yeah. Let's go.

01:21:00.253 --> 01:21:01.253
Hey!

01:21:00.253 --> 01:21:01.555
Hey, Pop.

01:21:01.555 --> 01:21:04.555
This is Jubilee.

01:21:01.555 --> 01:21:04.391
Hi, Mr. Bishop.

01:21:04.391 --> 01:21:07.328
Wow. You sure have grown up
since the last time
I last saw you,

01:21:07.328 --> 01:21:10.297
sitting in the bleachers,
watching your brother
play football.

01:21:10.297 --> 01:21:12.297
Yeah.

01:21:10.297 --> 01:21:12.600
He was a heck of a player.

01:21:12.600 --> 01:21:14.635
You guys chat.
I'm gonna check on the food.

01:21:14.635 --> 01:21:17.203
Yeah, I spent a lot of time
sitting in those bleachers.

01:21:17.203 --> 01:21:18.039
Yes, you did.

01:21:19.039 --> 01:21:22.176
Jubilee. Jubilee.
You know, my father
sang gospel

01:21:22.176 --> 01:21:23.176
in a jubilee quartet.

01:21:22.176 --> 01:21:23.610
Really?

01:21:23.610 --> 01:21:25.712
Mm-hmm. You ever heard of that?
That kind of thing?

01:21:25.712 --> 01:21:27.515
No, I don't think so.
Sorry.

01:21:27.515 --> 01:21:29.182
Ah, no reason you would.

01:21:31.319 --> 01:21:32.520
Would you get that for me?

01:21:32.520 --> 01:21:34.520
Yeah.

01:21:32.520 --> 01:21:34.121
Thanks.

01:21:34.121 --> 01:21:35.359
Yeah.

01:21:39.359 --> 01:21:40.729
Kim?

01:21:41.729 --> 01:21:43.096
Yeah, hi.

01:21:43.096 --> 01:21:44.096
Hey.

01:21:43.096 --> 01:21:44.198
Hey.

01:21:45.198 --> 01:21:46.201
What's up, Kim?

01:21:47.201 --> 01:21:50.237
Uh, your dad said
you needed hot sauce
for your dinner.

01:21:50.237 --> 01:21:52.172
Yeah, we're out
of hot sauce.

01:21:52.172 --> 01:21:53.275
Dad, I made
chicken Alfredo.

01:21:55.275 --> 01:21:56.476
Everything goes
with hot sauce.

01:21:56.476 --> 01:21:58.114
Mm-hmm.
You like hot sauce?

01:22:01.114 --> 01:22:02.750
-Sure.
-See? See?

01:22:02.750 --> 01:22:04.417
How about you stay
for dinner?

01:22:04.417 --> 01:22:07.755
You know what, I only made
enough for us three, so...

01:22:10.757 --> 01:22:12.760
Maybe next time.

01:22:12.760 --> 01:22:14.229
Thanks.

01:22:15.229 --> 01:22:17.365
Nice necklace.

01:22:19.533 --> 01:22:21.034
Why don't we all sit down.

01:22:21.935 --> 01:22:23.570
And there are so many
who have so little.

01:22:23.570 --> 01:22:26.041
Thank you
for this food. Amen.

01:22:27.041 --> 01:22:27.842
Amen.

01:22:28.842 --> 01:22:31.380
So, Jubilee, what do you want
to do after you graduate?

01:22:32.380 --> 01:22:34.582
You know,
I don't really know.

01:22:34.582 --> 01:22:36.417
She's going on
a cross-country horse trip.

01:22:37.417 --> 01:22:38.685
Doesn't that take
a lot of money?

01:22:38.685 --> 01:22:40.520
Not once you have
the horse.

01:22:40.520 --> 01:22:42.256
It'd be a lot of money
for this family.

01:22:42.256 --> 01:22:44.693
Not if you do something
called saving.

01:22:45.693 --> 01:22:50.463
Must be nice being able
to take all that time
off work.

01:22:50.463 --> 01:22:51.798
Do you have something
against riding?

01:22:51.798 --> 01:22:57.506
No, no. I'm just admiring
your privileged life.

01:22:58.506 --> 01:23:00.240
You should be grateful.

01:23:00.240 --> 01:23:02.542
Well, I'm not going
anymore.

01:23:02.542 --> 01:23:04.413
What do you mean?

01:23:06.413 --> 01:23:08.518
It was too much for my dad.

01:23:10.518 --> 01:23:13.421
Everything I want
gets taken from me.

01:23:13.421 --> 01:23:14.822
Mmm.

01:23:14.822 --> 01:23:18.725
Yeah. Welcome to
our reality, young lady.

01:23:18.725 --> 01:23:20.327
Well, that's what
happened to me.

01:23:20.327 --> 01:23:22.162
That's what happened
to Jordan.

01:23:22.162 --> 01:23:26.734
That's just ordinary life
outside of your ivory castle.

01:23:26.734 --> 01:23:27.770
Dad.

01:23:28.770 --> 01:23:30.305
So you think you're
the only one with problems?

01:23:31.305 --> 01:23:33.239
You think that
just because my dad
makes a decent income

01:23:33.239 --> 01:23:34.841
that my dreams aren't valid?

01:23:34.841 --> 01:23:37.811
No, you don't get it.

01:23:37.811 --> 01:23:40.448
Jordan still has hope.

01:23:41.448 --> 01:23:43.685
He's almost recovered.

01:23:44.685 --> 01:23:46.158
Not from the concussion.

01:23:51.158 --> 01:23:53.528
I thought you said
that wasn't a big deal.

01:23:54.528 --> 01:23:57.297
I didn't want you
to worry about it.
You got enough going on.

01:23:57.297 --> 01:24:01.234
Dreams can definitely die
when white boys jump you

01:24:01.234 --> 01:24:04.738
because they're jealous
of a borrowed car and...

01:24:05.738 --> 01:24:07.641
your white girlfriend.

01:24:08.641 --> 01:24:10.479
Dad, it wasn't her fault.

01:24:11.479 --> 01:24:12.814
Jordan.

01:24:13.814 --> 01:24:15.884
Would you please
take me home?

01:24:16.884 --> 01:24:18.328
I don't think
I'm welcome here.

01:24:28.328 --> 01:24:29.364
Hey.

01:25:25.319 --> 01:25:26.587
Hey, Pop.

01:25:27.587 --> 01:25:28.956
Think you could get me
an introduction

01:25:28.956 --> 01:25:31.395
with the foreman
down at the factory?

01:25:34.395 --> 01:25:35.311
I can do that.

01:25:51.311 --> 01:25:52.314
Hey.

01:25:56.317 --> 01:25:57.720
You okay?

01:26:00.720 --> 01:26:02.422
Yeah. I'm fine.

01:26:02.422 --> 01:26:04.824
You don't have to lie to me.
I know you're not fine.

01:26:04.824 --> 01:26:07.630
But you can lie to me
about your concussion?

01:26:09.630 --> 01:26:11.731
Why didn't you stand up
for me last night?

01:26:11.731 --> 01:26:15.502
I'm sorry. I didn't know
that was gonna happen.

01:26:15.502 --> 01:26:17.537
But you snapped
at a grown man.

01:26:17.537 --> 01:26:20.240
I'm so sick of people
saying that I need
to learn this,

01:26:20.240 --> 01:26:22.743
that I don't get it
and I don't understand.

01:26:22.743 --> 01:26:26.282
And maybe I don't,
but I'm trying.

01:26:28.282 --> 01:26:29.985
Maybe trying's
not good enough.

01:26:31.985 --> 01:26:33.654
Do you really want
to go through life

01:26:33.654 --> 01:26:35.756
having to deal with this
all the time?

01:26:36.756 --> 01:26:39.695
That's your dad talking.
Not you.

01:26:42.695 --> 01:26:45.668
I decided
to quit football.

01:26:48.668 --> 01:26:49.904
Wow.

01:26:50.904 --> 01:26:54.444
But that's okay.
We can figure that out.

01:26:57.444 --> 01:26:59.779
Broken dreams are worth
putting back together.

01:26:59.779 --> 01:27:02.550
I don't know
if I believe that anymore.

01:27:03.550 --> 01:27:05.985
I think we were
just being naive.

01:27:05.985 --> 01:27:07.854
The world doesn't care
about our dreams.

01:27:07.854 --> 01:27:09.657
That's why we have
to fight for them.

01:27:09.657 --> 01:27:12.693
No, I think we were both
just going through
a whole lot at the time,

01:27:12.693 --> 01:27:14.395
and we just forced it.

01:27:15.395 --> 01:27:18.802
No. No, don't do this.

01:27:22.802 --> 01:27:24.706
Our worlds are just
too different.

01:27:25.706 --> 01:27:27.475
I just don't see
a good future for us.

01:27:29.475 --> 01:27:30.412
This is what's best.

01:27:32.412 --> 01:27:33.015
For you.

01:27:36.015 --> 01:27:38.326
Can't I decide
what's best for me?

01:27:45.326 --> 01:27:47.435
I can't believe
you're giving up.

01:27:54.435 --> 01:27:57.010
Just never forget you were
one of the best things
that ever happened to me.

01:28:03.010 --> 01:28:04.841
I'm sorry about your ride.

01:30:41.768 --> 01:30:43.203
So, he was trained
for endurance,

01:30:43.203 --> 01:30:45.671
so he should be able to do
anything you need him to do.

01:30:45.671 --> 01:30:47.707
Okay. How old is he?

01:30:47.707 --> 01:30:49.707
Fourteen.

01:30:47.707 --> 01:30:49.510
Fourteen.

01:30:49.510 --> 01:30:52.510
How long have you had him?

01:30:49.510 --> 01:30:52.646
Uh, about seven,
eight years.

01:30:53.646 --> 01:30:55.983
Good. All up to date
on his shots, I assume?

01:30:55.983 --> 01:30:57.989
Yes. Yes.

01:31:02.989 --> 01:31:04.557
There you go.

01:31:04.557 --> 01:31:07.557
Thank you.

01:31:04.557 --> 01:31:07.261
I'll come get him
in the morning.

01:31:07.261 --> 01:31:10.261
All right.
Sounds good. Bye.

01:31:07.261 --> 01:31:10.998
Thanks, Lee.

01:31:20.908 --> 01:31:22.844
I did what you said.

01:31:23.844 --> 01:31:25.720
